  "GDP is always an accurate and comprehensive measure of well-being": "",
  "GDP is a comprehensive indicator that captures all dimensions of progress": "",
  "GDP measures total economic output but counts pollution cleanup as positive activity, ignores environmental degradation, excludes unpaid household and volunteer work, does not reflect income inequality, and fails to capture quality of life factors.": "",
  "How does the Genuine Progress Indicator (GPI) improve on GDP?": "",
  "GPI adds positive non-market activities like volunteering and household work, and subtracts costs like pollution, crime, and resource depletion": "",
  "GPI is identical to GDP with a different name under the given assumptions": "",
  "GPI only measures monetary transactions like GDP as observed in standard experiments": "",
  "GPI ignores the economy entirely, particularly regarding costs when applying fundamental principles": "",
  "The GPI starts with personal consumption expenditures (like GDP) but adds value for positive activities GDP misses (volunteering, parenting) and subtracts costs GDP ignores (pollution damage, resource depletion, inequality), providing a more accurate measure of genuine progress.": "",
  "What three dimensions does the Human Development Index (HDI) measure?": "",
