  "To calculate total ecological footprint, multiply the per capita footprint by the total population. Comparing total footprint to total biocapacity reveals whether a country has an ecological surplus (footprint < biocapacity) or deficit (footprint > biocapacity).": "",
  "What should comprehensive sustainability indicators measure?": "",
  "Only environmental quality indicators under equilibrium conditions": "",
  "Environmental health, economic viability, and social well-being together, reflecting the three pillars of sustainability": "",
  "Only one dimension of progress at a time when measured under controlled conditions": "",
  "Only economic growth and employment, particularly regarding education based on the prevailing evidence": "",
  "Comprehensive sustainability indicators must capture all three pillars simultaneously: environmental health (resource use, pollution, biodiversity), economic viability (income, employment, productivity), and social well-being (equity, health, education, governance).": "",
