  "Country X has a population of 50 million, a per capita ecological footprint of 8 gha, and a total biocapacity of 200 million gha. Calculate whether Country X has an ecological surplus or deficit and by how much.": "",
  "Cannot be calculated with the information provided": "",
  "Surplus of 200 million gha because biocapacity exceeds footprint": "",
  "Perfectly balanced because 50 million times 4 equals 200 million": "",
  "Deficit of 200 million gha because total footprint is 400 million gha (50M x 8) minus 200 million gha biocapacity": "",
  "Total ecological footprint = 50 million people x 8 gha/person = 400 million gha. Biocapacity = 200 million gha. Deficit = 400 - 200 = 200 million gha. Country X is consuming twice what its ecosystems can regenerate.": "",
  "Two countries have similar GDPs per capita. Country A has high income inequality (Gini = 0.55), poor air quality, low life expectancy, and high ecological footprint. Country B has low inequality (Gini = 0.25), clean air, high life expectancy, and moderate ecological footprint. How would GDP, HDI, and ecological footprint each rank these countries differently?": "",
